# Package Architecture

- Pick the smallest matching package archetype from `docs/architecture/doctrine/06-archetypes.md`
  before changing package or plugin structure.
- Keep folder roles aligned to `docs/architecture/doctrine/05-folder-structure.md`: `domain/`,
  `ports/`, `application/`, `adapters/`, `runtime/`, `presentation/`, `testing/`, `tests/`, and
  `examples/` have specific meanings.
- Preserve dependency direction from `docs/architecture/doctrine/05-folder-structure.md`: domain has
  no package implementation imports; application does not import adapters; presentation stays thin.
- Avoid doctrine anti-patterns listed in `docs/architecture/doctrine/09-anti-patterns-and-fitness-functions.md`,
  especially monolithic files, hidden globals, generic `utils`/`helpers`/`common` folders, and
  side effects outside edge files.
- Run or extend `tools/fitness/*` when a change touches an enforced architectural rule.
